Design: STSAssumeRoleToken generator (fixes #4752)

Root cause: STSSessionToken calls sts:GetSessionToken after AssumeRole.
AWS rejects GetSessionToken when caller holds temporary credentials
(session credentials from AssumeRole, or IRSA pod identity tokens).

Key design decisions:
- New generator instead of fixing STSSessionToken to preserve backwards
  compatibility and keep the two use-cases clearly separated.
- NewGeneratorSession called with role="" so base credentials are
  set up (secretRef or JWT/IRSA) without role assumption. AssumeRole
  is then performed explicitly via stscreds.NewAssumeRoleProvider,
  which allows passing Duration and ExternalID options.
- cfg.Credentials.Retrieve(ctx) triggers the actual sts:AssumeRole call
  and returns the temporary credentials directly — GetSessionToken is
  never called.
- Supports both static long-term credentials + role (the bug reporter's
  case) and IRSA/JWT + role (chain assumption).
- Role field is required (minLength=1); generator is named to make the
  AssumeRole semantics explicit and avoid confusion with STSSessionToken.
